ZZ    :wq
%
<c-o> In insert mode switch to normal mode for one command
%
L     jump to bottom of screen ("low")
M     jump to middle of screen ("middle")
H     jump to top of screen ("high")
%
zt    put this line at the 't'op of the screen
zb    put this line at the 'b'ottom of the screen
zz    put this line at the middle of the screen
%
]p    Paste text, aligning indentation with surroundings
%
aI    Parent indentation level text block
ii    Inner indentation level text block
%
:mksession ~/mysession.vim    Create a session
:source ~/mysession.vim       Restore session
vim -S ~/mysession.vim        Start vim and restore session
%
